# 9. たくさんの想いと共に

Nene: This audience is bigger than I was expecting...
Tsukasa: Yes. This is an official Shibuya event, after all.
Ichika: This feels so different from one of our usual shows...
An: Yeah, I know what you mean! The crowd always cheers and stuff during the events we perform in, but things are so quiet here.
Cast Member: I'm starting to get a little nervous...
Cast Member: What do I do if I forget my lines...?
Nene: Oh...
Band Member: I'm scared. What if we miss our cue to start playing? We might end up confusing the cast...
Cast Member: Deep breaths... Huff...
Nene: (Everyone's so tense.)
Nene: (Which makes sense... I mean, a lot of them are doing this for the first time.)
Nene: (What's the right thing to tell them in this situation?)
Airi: Don't worry!!
Cast Member: Huh?
Airi: Have confidence in the all the hard work you've put in until now. As long as you play the way you practiced, this show's gonna be absolutely awesome!
Airi: Your efforts are going to pay off! Believe in yourselves!
Tsukasa: Yes, Airi Momoi's absolutely right! You've all come such a long way.
Tsukasa: I know that for a fact, since I've been with you all since day one! You've all become wonderful actors!
An: Tenma...
An: In other words, instead of feeling scared or worried, we should be telling ourselves that we're gonna succeed, right?!
Ichika: I agree with that.
Ichika: Let's have confidence in our abilities, and give the audience a show they're going to remember!
Emu: Yeah! Let's send them all home smiling☆
Nene: (You guys...)
Nene: You're all right.
Nene: We aren't going up on that stage alone.
Nene: The cast, the band, the songwriters and everyone else...
Nene: All the people who were involved in making this show happen are by your side.
Nene: They're your friends and allies. So, don't worry.
Cast Member: Kusanagi...
Band Member: Right...!
Nene: Let's go out there and put on the best show ever!
Everyone: Yes! Yeah!
Announcement: Our special presentation of “A Dream On A Melody”, brought to you by the planning committee, will begin momentarily.
Kohane: ...! It's starting soon... I-I'm getting nervous...
Toya: Me too...
Akito: Wait, why are you guys feeling nervous?
Mizuki: When do we get to see the backgrounds you and the others made, Ena?
Ena: During the scene where the protagonist sneaks into town. I'm really proud of what we made, so get ready.
Kanade: You helped design the costumes, right, Mizuki?
Mizuki: Yup! I'm also really proud of what we made, so keep your eyes peeled♪
Minori: Oh, they're dimming the lights!
Haruka: Break a leg, you guys.
Young Lady: *Sigh* “I'm so bored...”
Young Lady: “I'm tired of sewing, playing with dolls and reading. It's all so dreary.”
Young Lady: “They say the outside world is full of dangers. I haven't the courage to go out, but...”
Young Lady: “But...”
Young Lady: “♪————...”
Toya: (The protagonist is feeling a mix of both fear and excitement regarding the outside world...)
Toya: (I see. So that's how she's chosen to express the feelings in this song.)
Nameless Musician: “♪————”
Music-loving Girl: “♪————”
Music-loving Girl: “Hehehe♪ I really love the way you sing, so I couldn't help but jump in!”
Nameless Musician: “Hehe. I also love the way you sing.”
Nameless Musician: “Do you also like this song?”
Young Lady: “Oh... A-Actually... This is my first time hearing it.”
Young Lady: “But I do think I enjoyed it... Now that I've heard you perform it.”
Nameless Musician: “Then, why don't I teach it to you? We can sing it together.”
Young Lady: “...! O-Okay!”
Shiho: (Let's go, everyone.)
Nameless Musician: “Look over here!”
Young Lady: “Wh-What's over there? Wow...!”
Young Lady: “This is incredible! So many people are singing in the plaza...!”
Ena: (Oh... That background...)
Kanade: It looks like a fun little town.
Mafuyu: *Nod*
Dancing Musician: “Hehehe. Hello there, young lady! Aren't you just the cutest?”
Dancing Musician: “I'm a musician who loves to dance and sing! Would you like to hear me sing something?”
Street Musician: “You should also listen to me! I guarantee you won't be disappointed!”
Dancing Musician: “♪————————”
Street Musician: “♪————~~~~~!”
Rui: (Okay, so far so good.)
Rui: (Everyone seems relaxed, their delivery sounds natural...)
Rui: (The band's putting on a wonderful performance, too. They're doing an impeccable job of showing how fun and free this town is, and how the protagonist's feelings are soaring.)
Rui: (But the hard part begins here.)
Rui: (Lulu decides that she also wants to become a musician after becoming friends with them. But the butler soon catches her sneaking out of the mansion.)
Rui: (She feels bad for making everyone worry, and decides to return to her boring old life.)
Rui: (This is your time to shine, Nene.)
Young Lady: “I'm so bored... More than ever before...”
Young Lady: “It's as though all the color has faded from the world.”
Young Lady: “After all, I know how wonderful music is now. I know how it can bring joy to others...”
Young Lady: “But now I'll never...”
???: “Let us see her!”
Young Lady: “...!”
Young Lady: “That voice... It came from outside the mansion. Could it be...?”
Young Lady: “They're all outside the gate!”
Tutor: “The young lady will no longer be setting foot outside of this mansion. I ask that you please disperse.”
Dancing Musician: “Is that what she said?”
Tutor: “Yes, she does not wish to see any of you ever again.”
Street Musician: “Ever again...?”
Nameless Musician: “♪————”
Young Lady: “Huh...?”
Young Lady: “That song... It's the first one I heard when...”
Nameless Musician: “Hey, can you hear me?! Let's sing together again!”
Nameless Musician: “♪————”
Young Lady: “...”
Street Musician: “♪————~~~!”
Street Musician: “Are you really going to let your dream end like this?”
Street Musician: “I don't think you will!”
Music-loving Girl: “I want to hear you sing more, Lulu!”
Young Lady: “But...”
Dancing Musician: “It's okay! Be brave!”
Dancing Musician: “Yes, pursuing your dream isn't easy! Neither is staying true to your feelings.”
Dancing Musician: “But you have all of us on your side!”
Dancing Musician: “♪————————!”
Saki: (Wow...!)
Saki: (She's channeling all of her feelings into the song I wrote!)
Saki: (Thank you so much, Airi...!!)
Young Lady: “All of you...”
Young Lady: “Thank you... For reminding me of the joy I felt when I first heard you all perform. For giving me the courage to move forward.”
Young Lady: “So...”
Young Lady: “Here's my response!”
Young Lady: “♪————”
Nene: (Thank you, everyone...)
Nene: (I promise to take all the feelings you've put into this show, and sing like I never have before!)
Young Lady: “♪————~~~”
Ichika: (Kusanagi...)
Minori: Whoa...
Haruka: Yeah...
Nameless Musician: “Wait, that song!”
Music-loving Girl: “Wow...!”
Street Musician: “Yes, it's Lulu!”
Tutor: “What...?! Was that really you just now? That was so beautiful...”
Young Lady: “Everyone!”
Dancing Musician: “Lulu!”
Young Lady: “I love singing more than anything!”
Young Lady: “I want my songs to make everyone around the world smile...”
Young Lady: “That's my dream. So...!”
Dancing Musician: “Yes, let's sing!”
Dancing Musician: “All of us. Together. Now and forever!”
Young Lady: “Yes!”
